24/03/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU security chief Javier Solana met with Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski on Thursday (23 March) to discuss reforms in the country and preparations for parliamentary elections. 
In particular, Solana mentioned the need for the adoption of legislation on police and judicial reforms. 
He also stressed the importance of conducting fair elections according to international standards. 
Separately, Buckovski discussed the issue of visa liberalisation with EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn. 
(EU Web site, Makfax, MIA, A1 TV - 23/03/06)
